  "name": "Wavelet Image",
  "summary": "Learn about .WI files and view a list of programs that open them.",
  "developer": "Corel",
  "technical_info": {
    "content": [
      "CorelDRAW, Photo-Paint, and Photo House allow users to export images as WI files. WI files may contain 8-bit grayscale or 24-bit RGB images. They must be a minimum of 16 pixels in size, and they can be a maximum of 2,048 pixels in size.",
      "NOTE: The WI format replaced the .WVL format."
    ]
  },
  "how_to_open": {
    "instructions": [
      "You can open a WI file with CorelDRAW and Corel Photo-Paint, which are included in the CorelDRAW Graphics Suite (Windows)."
    ]
  },
  "how_to_convert": {
    "instructions": [
      "CorelDRAW can convert WI files to many more common image formats, including:",
      ".JPG - JPEG Image",
      ".PNG - Portable Network Graphic",
      ".BMP - Bitmap Image",
      ".GIF - Graphical Interchange Format",
      ".SVG - Scalable Vector Graphics File",
      ".PDF - Portable Document Format",
      ".TGA - Targa Graphic",
      ".TIF - Tagged Image File Format"
    ]
  },
